ning with the star-nosed mole, Catania reveals what the creature’s nasal star is actually for, and what this tells us about how brains work. He explores how the deceptive hunting strategy of tentacled snakes leads prey straight to their mouths, how eels use electricity to control other animals, and why emerald jewel wasps make zombies out of cockroaches. He also solves the enigma of worm grunting by teaming up with professional worm grunters. Catania demonstrates the merits of approaching science with an open mind, considers the role played by citizen scientists, and illustrates that most animals have incredible, hidden abilities that defy our imagination.Examining some strange and spectacular creatures, Great Adaptations offers a wondrous journey into nature’s grand designs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 7aSCIENCE / Natural History.2bisacsh  aAnurag Agrawal.  aApalachicola National Forest.  aAudrey Revell.  aCharles Darwin.  aDavid Hu.  aGary Revell.  aHow to Walk on Water and Climb Up Walls.  aMonarchs and Milkweed.  aSara Lewis.  aSilent Sparks.  aadaptation.  aanimal behavior.  abehavior.  abiological detective.  abiology.  abrain.  acitizen scientists.  aearthworm.  aelectric eel.  aelectroreception.  aemerald jewel wasp.  aethology.  aevolution.  aneocortex.  anervous system.  aneuroethology.  aneuroscience.  apredator.  aprey.  areproduction.  asensory system.  asensory.  ashrews.  asomatosensory.  astar-nosed mole.  atentacled snakes.  aworm bait.  aworm grunting.  aworms.  azombie cockroach.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe 